what would make a newborn baby's skin break out he is a week old and has blotches all over his body red blotches it is hard to tell if it bothering him he is a little fussy an infant's skin goes through many changes at birth and for about the first week of life his skin was probably very smooth and velvety and may even have felt a little greasy after the first week several skin conditions are common erythema toxicum is probably what your son is having it is a benign skin eruption not related to any allergic reaction and will resolve on its own another common infant skin condition is infant acne it can begin about weeks old and last as long as months it is normal and doesn't need any treatment it is generally believed to be caused by maternal hormones transferred just before birth Acne Obstetrics Cephalic disorder Androgen insensitivity syndrome Psoriasis Breastfeeding Childbirth Urinary incontinence Infant Hormone replacement therapy (trans) Allergy Scar Jaundice Prostate cancer Pregnancy Hypoglycemia Skin Herpes simplex virus Puberty Congenital hypothyroidism Dandruff Birth weight Cancer Vitamin D Pneumonia Insulin Eczema Tocopherol Sex assignment Urticaria Group A streptococcal infection Phimosis Lipoid congenital adrenal hyperplasia Medical analysis of circumcision Postpartum depression Sexual differentiation Radiation therapy Menstrual cycle Cytomegalovirus Elephant Callus Human skin color Dexamethasone Fecal incontinence Testosterone Cheetah Polycystic ovary syndrome Congenital adrenal hyperplasia Non-Hodgkin's lymphoma Cryptorchidism Glucocorticoid Growth hormone deficiency Conjunctivitis Birthmark Folic acid Rosacea Intact dilation and extraction Prenatal diagnosis Breech birth Syphilis Diarrhea Penis Food allergy Coeliac disease Infant mortality Fetus Metastasis Abortion debate Tuberous sclerosis Abortion Cellulitis Infant baptism Circumcision Glossary of medical terms related to communications disorders Stuttering Intersex surgery Chlorpromazine Amiodarone 